// =================================================
// ELEMENT RELATIONSHIPS
// =================================================

/*
=========================================================
STUDENT INSTRUCTIONS FOR SHOWING RELATIONSHIPS (NON-RENDERING COMMENTS)
======================================================

   - Add directional arrows to indicate causal relationships.
   • Label each arrow with polarity (+ or -).
   • Indicate delays where relevant (e.g., "+ delay", "- long delay").
   - Use a comment // under each relationship to describe the relationships.
   - Use comments for explanatory notes, questions, and additional information.
   - Identify reinforcing (R) and balancing (B) loops using subgraphs.
   • Focus on structural, population-level mechanisms.
   • Do NOT default to individual behavior as an explanation.

*/

/* =================================================
EXAMPLE OF FORMATTING RELATIONSHIPS - REMOVE THIS EXAMPLE WHEN YOU SUBMIT YOUR SYSTEM MAP
==================================================
Note in this example that the relationship is labeled with a polarity and a delay, and that there is a comment below the relationship that describes the relationship. References to support the relationship should be included. You should do this for all of your relationships in your system map. 

*/


Public_health_surveillance_capacity -> federal_discretionary_health_funding [label="+ long delay"];
// This relationship indicates that higher public health surveillance capacity leads to increased federal discretionary health funding, but with a delay due to the time it takes for data collection, analysis, and reporting to influence funding decisions.

//Harrington, M. L., Chen, S., & Okafor, D. R. (2024). Federal fiscal responses to expanded epidemiological surveillance infrastructure: A longitudinal analysis of discretionary spending patterns, 2010–2023. American Journal of Fake Health Policy, 18(3), 112–129. https://doi.org/10.1097/ajhp.0000000000000XXX

federal discretionary_health_funding -> community_health_program_capacity [label="+ short delay"];
// This relationship indicates that increased federal discretionary health funding leads to increased community-based health program capacity, but with a delay due to the time it takes for funding to be allocated, programs to be developed, and staff to be hired and trained.

/* =========================================================
END OF EXAMPLE OF FORMATTING RELATIONSHIPS - REMOVE THIS EXAMPLE WHEN YOU SUBMIT YOUR SYSTEM MAP
=========================================================
*/
